gomodel:SYNGO_4128  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig S1C: Biochemical fractionation indicates enrichment of Arf6 at pH6 similarly to the SV protein synaptophysin.\n\nFig S1A: Endogenous Arf6 colocalizes with both presynaptic (Synaptophysin) and postsynaptic (Homer1) markers in primary rat hippocampal neurons (17 days in vitro, DIV) and triple labelling showed expression of the small GTPase at the presynaptic and postsynaptic site of single synaptic puncta.\n\nFig S1B: Arf6 immunoreaction product colocalises with Vglut1 and lies adjacent to homer.\n\n18/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper does not comment on the specificity of the antibody used.. Experimental description: Sprague-Dawley rats were from Charles River were used in this study." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4128" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

